<paragraph blockId="50.[151,503,758,780]" box="[151,503,758,780]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Species included: 2 (Afrotropical).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,825,958]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Synapomorphies: Sternite 5 expanded, 4–5 with modified setae (23) and basiphallus with expanded subdivided mid section and cordiform extension of distiphallus (46). The systematic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirk-Spriggs &amp; Wiegmann" authorityYear="2013" box="[1075,1177,861,885]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonzo">
<emphasis box="[1075,1094,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1110,1177,862,885]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">gonzo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas" authorityYear="1974" box="[1236,1387,861,885]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternithrix">
<emphasis box="[1236,1255,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1271,1387,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">sternithrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can only be fully assessed as part of a more extensive molecular study. They are here tentatively ascribed to the speciesgroup based on the aforementioned synapomorphies, but differ externally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
